## Key Backend Conventions
- All models inherit `core.models.BaseModel`
- Soft delete via `SoftDeleteMixin` — never hard delete
- Audit fields (`created_by`, `updated_by`) auto-filled via `AuditMixin`
- FilterSet classes only — no raw query params
- Dual FK serializer fields: `<field>_id` (write) + `<field>` (nested read)
- Custom `create()`/`update()` for nested children
- Zero N+1 — `select_related`/`prefetch_related` always enforced
- Standardised error response: `{ success, message, errors }` via `core.exceptions`

## Frontend Structure
```
src/
├── app/store.ts + hooks.ts
├── services/api.ts          # Axios instance with JWT refresh
├── features/<feature>/      # One folder per domain
│   ├── types.ts
│   ├── <feature>Slice.ts
│   ├── <feature>Service.ts
│   └── components/
└── components/shared/       # Canonical shared components — never reimplement
```

## Key Frontend Conventions
- Redux Toolkit for all server state
- Axios via `services/api.ts` only — never direct fetch/axios calls
- All UI via `src/components/shared/` — Text, Button, FormField, DataTable, Modal,
  PageHeader, EmptyState, LoadingSpinner, ErrorBanner, StatusBadge
- React.memo + useCallback + useMemo on every component
- camelCase variables, PascalCase components
- No `any` TypeScript types
- API errors always typed as `{ success: false, message: string, errors: Record<string, string[]> }`

